# Image QA Checklist

Run before every PR or sprint completion.

## Filenames
- [ ] All lowercase
- [ ] All hyphenated (no spaces, underscores)
- [ ] No typos in filenames
- [ ] All .webp format (except OG = .jpg, logos = .svg)
- [ ] Names are descriptive with service + location

## Alt Text
- [ ] Every meaningful image has alt text
- [ ] No duplicated words in any alt text
- [ ] No generic or empty alt on meaningful images
- [ ] No alt text exceeds 125 characters
- [ ] No alt text truncated mid-sentence
- [ ] Decorative images have alt="" (empty string)

## Next.js Image Props
- [ ] Every image has width and height set
- [ ] Every image has sizes prop for its layout position
- [ ] priority={true} on first hero image only
- [ ] No priority prop on any other image
- [ ] No loading="eager" anywhere
- [ ] quality={85} on photo images
- [ ] blurDataURL + placeholder="blur" on hero images

## Schema
- [ ] ImageObject added to Service schema on service pages
- [ ] ImageObject added to Article schema on blog posts
- [ ] OG image referenced in page metadata export

## OG Images
- [ ] Every page has unique OG image
- [ ] All OG images 1200×630px JPG
- [ ] Stored at /public/images/og/[page-slug].jpg
- [ ] og:image meta tag references absolute URL

## Performance
- [ ] Hero image = LCP element with priority={true}
- [ ] No other image has priority={true}
- [ ] Card images under 50KB
- [ ] Hero images under 150KB
- [ ] No CLS — width/height always set
- [ ] Lighthouse Performance 90+
